# kexec

> Directly reboot into a new kernel
> More information: https://manned.org/kexec

- Load a new kernel:

`kexec -l {string value: path/to/kernel} --initrd={string value: path/to/initrd} --command-line={string value: arguments}`

- Load a new kernel with current boot parameters:

`kexec -l {string value: path/to/kernel} --initrd={string value: path/to/initrd} --reuse-cmdline`

- Execute a currently loaded kernel:

`kexec -e`

- Unload current kexec target kernel:

`kexec -u`
